  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nWhy should this feature exist?\r\nFor many reasons people create their own private test network to test their applications, whether it is a contract, wallet or any other applications that use the blockchain.\r\n \r\nWhat are the use-cases?\r\nWhen testing blockchain related stuff that need to mine block repeatedly and they do not care about the actual process of the mining and only the applicative part of the blockchain the fact the the difficulty rises is slowing down the testing process and is not required.\r\n\r\nTesting wallets for example.\r\n\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\n\r\nI was thinking we can add this to the chain config as a boolean, something like \"static_difficulty\" (`params/config.go`)\r\nand then inside the `CalcDifficulty` function in `conesnsus.go` we can check the config, and if the config contains the flag we will just return 0.\r\n\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature?\r\n\r\nYes.",
